\begin{center}
{
\Large
Languages Isomorphic to JSON
}
\vspace{0.1in}
\end{center}

\begin{note}
In mathematics, the word \emph{isomorphic} means that two objects are ``the same in every meaningful way.''
(In greek, \emph{iso} means ``same'' and \emph{morph} means ``shape''.)
In programming, we call two languages isomorphic if they can be easily converted back and forth between each other without any loss of meaning.
\end{note}
